[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEDUP_TOKEN: b38823cc610751ee[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA Jazzer fuzzing run detected a Server Side Request Forgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m issue when [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing a ZIP archive with Apache Commons Compress. The fuzzer input caused a call [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto [0m[1;35mURL.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, attempting to connect to “jazze.com:[0m[1;36m80[0m[39m”. Jazzer’s SSRF [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msanitizer prevented the connection and raised a `FuzzerSecurityIssueMedium`, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msignaling that untrusted data was used to drive an outbound network request.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue type: Server Side Request Forgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Exception:  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueMedium: Server Side Request [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mForgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Attempted connection to: jazze.com:[0m[1;36m80[0m[39m  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Stack trace highlights:  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `ServerSideRequestForgery.checkSsrf`  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `ServerSideRequestForgery.checkSsrfSocket`  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. `java.net.Socket.connect`  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. `java.net.URL.openStream`  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. `org.apache.commons.compress.archivers.zip.ZipFile.readCentralDirectoryEntry` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m. `CompressZipFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput`  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- What happened:  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  While exercising the ZIP‐file parsing code, the fuzzer supplied input that [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minduced the `ZipFile` class to treat part of the archive data as a URL. During the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcentral‐directory reading phase, `[0m[1;35mURL.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` was invoked on untrusted data, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresulting in an outbound HTTP connection attempt to “jazze.com:[0m[1;36m80[0m[39m.”  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Why it matters:  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  If untrusted archive contents control network destinations, an attacker could [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcoerce the application into making arbitrary requests on its behalf. This can lead [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto exfiltration of internal data or unauthorized access to internal services.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Key areas for investigation:  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The ZIP parsing logic in `org.apache.commons.compress.archivers.zip.ZipFile`, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mespecially the `readCentralDirectoryEntry` and `populateFromCentralDirectory` [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethods where URL resources are resolved.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Any code that treats ZIP‐entry names or metadata as URLs or resource locators. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The behavior of `[0m[1;35mjava.net.URL.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` when given archive‐derived strings.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Integration of Jazzer’s `ServerSideRequestForgery` sanitizer in the test [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mharness and production code, to understand what network calls are allowed or [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblocked.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`CompressZipFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to see how inputs [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare fed into the zip parser and whether additional sanitization steps are missing. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis issue suggests that unvalidated archive contents can drive network operations.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA thorough review of URL resolution and external resource loading in the ZIP parser[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis needed to understand the full impact and surface area.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== Java Exception: com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueMedium: [0m     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m896[0m[39m:    private [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal SeekableByteChannel channel, final String [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchannelDescription, final Charset encoding, final boolean useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m897[0m[39m:            final boolean closeOnError, final boolean ignoreLocalFileHeader[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m900[0m[39m:        this.zipEncoding = [0m[1;35mZipEncodingHelper.getZipEncoding[0m[1;39m([0m[39mencoding[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m901[0m[39m:        this.useUnicodeExtraFields = useUnicodeExtraFields;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m902[0m[39m:        this.archive = channel;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m903[0m[39m:        boolean success = false;[0m                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m905[0m[39m:            final Map<ZipArchiveEntry, NameAndComment> entriesWithoutUTF8Flag =[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mpopulateFromCentralDirectory[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root‐cause analysis  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The SSRF arises in `[0m[1;35mZipFile.readCentralDirectoryEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, lines ~[0m[1;36m1550[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m1560[0m[39m: [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39many entry comment beginning with “http…” is treated as a URL and fetched [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munconditionally via `new [0m[1;35mURL[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommentString[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. Untrusted archive data [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdrives an outbound network request.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Design of the patch  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Introduce a feature‐flag in `ZipFile` to control remote comment fetching:  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Add a private boolean field `allowRemoteCommentFetch` to `ZipFile`.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Default it to **false** to opt out of remote fetch by default [0m[1;39m([0m[39mclosing the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSSRF vector[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Extend the public Builder API so users who truly require remote comment fetch[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcan explicitly enable it:  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - In `ZipFile.Builder`, add method  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         `public Builder [0m[1;35msetAllowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean allow[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Store the flag in the Builder.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Have `[0m[1;35mBuilder.get[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` call the new `[0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` constructor, passing [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`allowRemoteCommentFetch`.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Modify deprecated constructors to continue working, with default [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`allowRemoteCommentFetch = false`.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   D. Guard the HTTP‐fetch block in `readCentralDirectoryEntry`:  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      String commentString = [0m[1;35mentryEncoding.decode[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcomment[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mallowRemoteCommentFetch[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          && [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"http://"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"https://"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m original fetch logic[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;35mze.setComment[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommentString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - If the flag is false [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, skip URL construction entirely.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   E. Update constructor signatures:  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Change the private constructor  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        `[0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel, String, Charset, boolean [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39museUnicodeExtraFields, boolean closeOnError, boolean ignoreLocalFileHeader[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        to also accept `boolean allowRemoteCommentFetch`.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Assign the parameter to the new field.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   F. Maintain backward compatibility:  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - All existing callers [0m[1;39m([0m[39mBuilder prior to this change, deprecated [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstructors[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m will not fetch remote content unless they explicitly use the new [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBuilder method.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - No test code or harness modifications required; default behavior is now [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSSRF‐safe.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Step‐by‐step implementation  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. In `ZipFile` class, declare:  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[39m** If true, entry comments starting with [0m[1;35mHTTP[0m[1;39m([0m[39mS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m will be fetched. *[0m[35m/[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      private final boolean allowRemoteCommentFetch;[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Modify the private constructor at line ~[0m[1;36m896[0m[39m to take the new flag:  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      private [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel channel,[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                      String channelDescription,[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                      Charset encoding,[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                      boolean useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                      boolean closeOnError,[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                      boolean ignoreLocalFileHeader,[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                      boolean allowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m existing assignments[0m[33m...[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          this.allowRemoteCommentFetch = allowRemoteCommentFetch;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m existing init logic[0m[33m...[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Update all calls to this constructor:  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - In `[0m[1;35mBuilder.get[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, change from  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        `return new [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mactualChannel, actualDescription, [0m[1;35mgetCharset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39museUnicodeExtraFields, closeOnError, ignoreLocalFileHeader[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        to  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        `return new [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mactualChannel, actualDescription, [0m[1;35mgetCharset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39museUnicodeExtraFields, closeOnError, ignoreLocalFileHeader, [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - In each deprecated constructor, add `false` as the last argument. E.g.:  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath path, String encoding, boolean useUnicodeExtraFields, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboolean ignoreLocalFileHeader[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mnewReadByteChannel[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mpath.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, encoding, [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39museUnicodeExtraFields, true,[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 ignoreLocalFileHeader, false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. In `ZipFile.Builder`, add:  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      private boolean allowRemoteCommentFetch = false;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      public Builder [0m[1;35msetAllowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean allow[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          this.allowRemoteCommentFetch = allow;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return this;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. In `[0m[1;35mreadCentralDirectoryEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` around line [0m[1;36m1550[0m[39m, wrap the URL fetch:  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      String commentString = [0m[1;35mentryEncoding.decode[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcomment[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mallowRemoteCommentFetch[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          && [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"http://"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"https://"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          try [0m[1;39m([0m[39mInputStream is = new [0m[1;35mURL[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommentString[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              ByteArrayOutputStream bos = new [0m[1;35mByteArrayOutputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[1;35mIOUtils.copy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mis, bos[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              commentString = new [0m[1;35mString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mbos.toByteArray[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mStandardCharsets.UTF_8[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mIOException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m swallow[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;35mze.setComment[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommentString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By default, remote comment fetching is disabled, immediately eliminating [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muntrusted URL open calls and SSRF in fuzzing or production.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing public and deprecated APIs remain intact; no harness or test changes [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrequired.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We preserve the ability to fetch remote resources for ZIP comments as an [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexplicit, opt‐in feature for those who rely on it.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fix is localized: only `ZipFile` core logic and its Builder are modified; [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mno utility classes, tests, or external libraries are touched.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential side effects and mitigation  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Feature change: users upgrading to the new library will see ZIP comments that [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontain URLs no longer auto‐expanded. Mitigation: document the new [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35msetAllowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtrue[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in migration notes.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Unaffected functionality: all non‐URL comments parse as before, and local file[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheader parsing remains unchanged.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. References  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Similar pattern in other libraries: e.g., disabling JAR manifest `Class‐Path` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremote downloads via an opt‐in flag.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Tests for URL comment fetching [0m[1;39m([0m[39mif any[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m can explicitly call [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mBuilder.setAllowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtrue[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to re‐enable the old behavior.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mile.jav[0m[1;92ma:1329[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39morg.apache.commons.compress.archivers.zip.ZipFile.<init>[0m[1;39m([0m[39mZipFile.jav[0m[1;92ma:905[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39morg.apache.commons.compress.archivers.zip.ZipFile.<init>[0m[1;39m([0m[39mZipFile.jav[0m[1;92ma:971[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39morg.apache.commons.compress.archivers.zip.ZipFile.<init>[0m[1;39m([0m[39mZipFile.jav[0m[1;92ma:938[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39morg.apache.commons.compress.archivers.zip.ZipFile.<init>[0m[1;39m([0m[39mZipFile.jav[0m[1;92ma:876[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m[1;35mCompressZipFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCompressZipFuzzer.jav[0m[1;92ma:30[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEDUP_TOKEN: b38823cc610751ee[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn Apache Commons Compress ZIP-file handling routine triggered a Jazzer fuzzer [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecurity alert for Server-Side Request Forgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when a ZIP entry comment [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbeginning with “http” caused a remote URL fetch. To mitigate this, the submitted [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch introduced a new boolean flag [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`allowRemoteCommentFetch`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m—defaulting to [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfalse—via the `ZipFile.Builder` and propagated it through constructors to [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconditionally disable [0m[1;35mHTTP[0m[1;39m([0m[39mS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m comment fetching. After applying the patch, the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproject failed to compile under Maven/Javac due to several constructor signature [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmismatches between `String` and `Charset` parameters.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The Jazzer fuzzer detected an SSRF violation [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`FuzzerSecurityIssueMedium`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhile processing a ZIP archive.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stack trace pinpoints `ZipFile.readCentralDirectoryEntry` invoking `new [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mURL[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommentString[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` if a comment starts with “http” or “https.”  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Requests to external addresses derived from untrusted ZIP comments pose a [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecurity risk by potentially exposing internal services or sensitive data.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Important Observations  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The remote fetch logic is embedded directly in [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ZipFile.populateFromCentralDirectory` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m1548[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - There is no existing configuration or flag to disable the [0m[1;35mHTTP[0m[1;39m([0m[39mS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m comment [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfetching behavior.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The vulnerability is triggered via untrusted data [0m[1;39m([0m[39mZIP entry comment[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, not via[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39many test harness issue.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added a private boolean field `allowRemoteCommentFetch` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault `false`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ZipFile.Builder`.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Created a builder method `[0m[1;35msetAllowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to expose the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mflag.  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Updated the primary `ZipFile` constructors to accept `allowRemoteCommentFetch`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand stored it in the `ZipFile` instance.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Modified the code detecting [0m[1;35mHTTP[0m[1;39m([0m[39mS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m comments to check [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`allowRemoteCommentFetch` before opening the URL stream:  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mallowRemoteCommentFetch[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         && [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"http://"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"https://"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         try [0m[1;39m([0m[39mInputStream is = new [0m[1;35mURL[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommentString[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Adjusted all constructor calls—including deprecated overloads—to pass the new [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mflag [0m[1;39m([0m[39malways `false` by default[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Patch Application Result  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - During `mvn package`, compilation failed with three errors in `ZipFile.java` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mat lines [0m[1;36m867[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m946[0m[39m, and [0m[1;36m979[0m[39m:  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     incompatible types: java.lang.String cannot be converted to [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mjava.nio.charset.Charset[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     incompatible types: java.lang.String cannot be converted to [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mjava.nio.charset.Charset[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     incompatible types: java.nio.charset.Charset cannot be converted to [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mjava.lang.String[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - These errors indicate mismatches in constructor parameter lists—some [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstructors still expect a `String` encoding, others a `Charset`. The patch did [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnot align all overloads and call sites to the updated signatures.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Code Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The group of `ZipFile` constructors handling `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel, String, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCharset, boolean, boolean, boolean[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` vs. `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel, String, String, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboolean, boolean, boolean[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. All overloads must be reconciled.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The deprecated constructors around lines [0m[1;36m857[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m894[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m935[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m979[0m[39m where the new [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboolean was appended but types were not harmonized.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Invocation sites in `[0m[1;35mBuilder.build[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and other internal factory methods that [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcreate `ZipFile` instances without the new flag or with the wrong parameter types. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo speculation on root causes or proposed fixes is included; the report is limited [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto observing the SSRF alert, the attempted mitigation via a feature flag, and the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresulting compile-time signature mismatches.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m912[0m[39m:            throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Error reading Zip content from "[0m[39m + [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchannelDescription, e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m913[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m finally [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m914[0m[39m:            this.closed = !success;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m915[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!success && closeOnError[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m916[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35morg.apache.commons.io.IOUtils.closeQuietly[0m[1;39m([0m[39marchive[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m917[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m918[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m919[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m920[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root cause analysis  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The last patch introduced a [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m-argument core constructor for `ZipFile` that [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtakes a `Charset` plus the new `allowRemoteCommentFetch` flag.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All of the deprecated public constructors [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhich supply a `String` encoding[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstill delegate to a [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnonexistent[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m constructor that takes `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mString, String, boolean, boolean[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m, boolean[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. As a result, those overloads now [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhave no matching target, and the compiler complains about “String cannot be [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconverted to Charset” and vice versa.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In addition, one call site in `[0m[1;35mBuilder.get[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` was correctly updated to call [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe new [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m-arg `Charset`-based constructor, but the old [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m-arg invocation still [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremains elsewhere.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Strategy to fix  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Reintroduce a [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m-argument private constructor overload that accepts a `String`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mencoding and the new boolean flag, and forwards to the existing `Charset`-based [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcore constructor. This restores the implicit “String→Charset” conversion used by [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mall deprecated overloads.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Update every delegating constructor [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe public deprecated ones[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m so that they[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdelegate to this new [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m-arg `String` overload, supplying `false` as the default for [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`allowRemoteCommentFetch`.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Ensure every explicit `new [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` invocation—including in [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mBuilder.get[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`—is updated to call the correct overload, passing the new flag in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe last position.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Detailed steps  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. In `ZipFile.java`, insert a new private constructor immediately before [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mafter[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m the existing `private [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel, String, Charset, …[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblock:[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         * Internal constructor for callers that supply a String-encoded charset[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         * and must propagate the allowRemoteCommentFetch flag.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        private [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal SeekableByteChannel channel,[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                        final String channelDescription,[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                        final String encoding,[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                        final boolean useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                        final boolean closeOnError,[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                        final boolean ignoreLocalFileHeader,[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                        final boolean allowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m)[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[39mchannel,[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 channelDescription,[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 [0m[1;35mCharsets.toCharset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mencoding, Builder.DEFAULT_CHARSET[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 closeOnError,[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 ignoreLocalFileHeader,[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 allowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. In every deprecated public constructor that takes a `String` encoding:[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Change its `[0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` invocation to include the extra [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`allowRemoteCommentFetch` boolean [0m[1;39m([0m[39malways `false` by default[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - For example:[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        - The `Path`-based overload becomes[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          ```java[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath path,[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                         String encoding,[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                         boolean useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                         boolean ignoreLocalFileHeader[0m[1;39m)[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                  throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mnewReadByteChannel[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   [0m[1;35mpath.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   encoding,[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   true,[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   ignoreLocalFileHeader,[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          ```[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        - The [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-arg `SeekableByteChannel` overload becomes[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          ```java[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel channel,[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                         String channelDescription,[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                         String encoding,[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                         boolean useUnicodeExtraFields[0m[1;39m)[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                  throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[39mchannel,[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   channelDescription,[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   encoding,[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   false,[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   false,[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          ```[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        - The [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m-arg and [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-arg `SeekableByteChannel` constructors already cascade [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthrough the above [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-arg overload, so no further change is needed there.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. In the builder logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mZipFile.Builder.get[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, replace the old [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m-arg call:[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```diff[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        -    return new [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mactualChannel,[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        -                       actualDescription,[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        -                       [0m[1;35mgetCharset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        -                       useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        -                       closeOnError,[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        -                       ignoreLocalFileHeader[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        +    return new [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mactualChannel,[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        +                       actualDescription,[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        +                       [0m[1;35mgetCharset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        +                       useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        +                       closeOnError,[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        +                       ignoreLocalFileHeader,[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        +                       allowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Confirm that the HTTP‐fetch logic still checks `allowRemoteCommentFetch` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore opening URLs:[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mallowRemoteCommentFetch[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            && [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"http://"[0m[1;39m)[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             || [0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"https://"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            try [0m[1;39m([0m[39mInputStream is = new [0m[1;35mURL[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommentString[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                …[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. Rebuild with Maven to ensure all constructor signatures now resolve correctly[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand no tests are broken.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Why this approach  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Restores the dropped “String → Charset” overload that was implicitly relied [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mupon by the deprecated constructors, eliminating the type‐mismatch errors without [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtouching external code or the fuzz harness.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Leaves the new `allowRemoteCommentFetch` flag in place, preserving the SSRF [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmitigation.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Minimally invasive: only adds one small private helper constructor and adjusts[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting delegations. All existing functionality and public API semantics remain [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munchanged [0m[1;39m([0m[39mapart from the new builder flag[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Matches the existing pattern elsewhere in `commons-compress` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mString‐→Charset [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconversion constructors[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential side effects & mitigation  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No change to any public API or test code beyond the introduction of the new [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuilder method and flag. All deprecated constructors still work as before.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Only internal constructor chaining is altered. No additional logic paths are [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintroduced.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If any third‐party code used the deprecated constructors, their behavior is [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munaffected [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthey still use `false` for remote‐fetch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m[12/21/25 19:44:22][0m[2;36m [0m[34mINFO    [0m Prism Supervisor Routing: TeamStatus.EVALUATE -> TeamStatus.ANALYZE                  ]8;id=877708;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py\[2m__init__.py[0m]8;;\[2m:[0m]8;id=779130;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py#160\[2m160[0m]8;;\
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0mn evals: [1;36m3[0m, patch status: PatchStatus.UNCOMPILABLE[1m)[0m                                 [2m               [0m
