[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn SSRF [0m[1;39m([0m[39mServer-Side Request Forgery[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m finding was raised by Jazzer when the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ZipFile` class opened URLs extracted from a ZIP entry’s comment. To mitigate this,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma patch was introduced in `ZipFile.java`, adding a boolean flag [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`allowRemoteCommentFetch` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and guarding the remote fetch logic [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbehind it. After applying the patch, the project failed to compile with an error in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ZipFile.java`:  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincompatible types: java.nio.charset.Charset cannot be converted to [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mjava.lang.String[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis indicates a mismatch between constructor signatures that take `Charset` versus[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthose taking `String`.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A Jazzer security sanitizer raised `FuzzerSecurityIssueMedium: Server Side [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRequest Forgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Stack trace shows it originates from `ZipFile.readCentralDirectoryEntry`, where a[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mZIP entry’s comment beginning with “[0m[4;94mhttp://[0m[39m” or “[0m[4;94mhttps://[0m[39m” triggers a network [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrequest [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`new [0m[1;35mURL[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommentString[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer input caused an attempted connection to an external host, flagging [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSSRF potential.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `ZipFile.Builder` a new field `allowRemoteCommentFetch` was added [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault = [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfalse[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with a setter.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All existing constructors of `ZipFile` were modified to accept an additional [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`boolean allowRemoteCommentFetch` parameter, defaulting it to `false` for [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeprecated and single-argument constructors.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The core constructor and ZIP parsing logic were updated to store this flag and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monly perform `new [0m[1;35mURL[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommentString[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` when it is `true`.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A new private overload was added to bridge constructors taking a `String [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mencoding` plus the new flag.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBuild Result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Maven compilation fails at `ZipFile.java:[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m1000[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m61[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, complaining that a `Charset`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis being passed where a `String` was expected.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This stems from a call site [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m1000[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m invoking a constructor whose [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msignature expects a `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel, String, String, boolean, boolean, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboolean, boolean[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` but is being supplied a `Charset` object instead of a `String`.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All overloaded `ZipFile` constructors and their parameter types [0m[1;39m([0m[39mespecially the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdistinction between `String encoding` vs. `Charset encoding`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The builder’s `[0m[1;35mget[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method and its invocation of `new [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, ensuring [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marguments match updated constructor signatures.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The lines around the reported compile error [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnear line [0m[1;36m1000[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to realign the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstructor call that passes a `Charset` where a `String` is now expected.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Any additional call sites [0m[1;39m([0m[39moutside the `Builder`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that instantiate `ZipFile` [0m     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/main/java/org/apache/commons/compress/archivers/zip/ZipFile.jav[0m[1;92ma:1549[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1560[0m      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1550[0m[39m:        String commentString = [0m[1;35mentryEncoding.decode[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcomment[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1560[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mze.setComment[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcommentString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/main/java/org/apache/commons/compress/archivers/zip/ZipFile.jav[0m[1;92ma:269[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m273[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m269[0m[39m:    private static final String DEFAULT_CHARSET_NAME = [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mStandardCharsets.UTF_8.name[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m270[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m271[0m[39m:    private static final EnumSet<StandardOpenOption> READ = [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mEnumSet.of[0m[1;39m([0m[39mStandardOpenOption.READ[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m272[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m273[0m[39m:    private static final int HASH_SIZE = [0m[1;36m509[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The compilation error stems from the Builder#get method invoking a [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msix-argument `ZipFile` constructor:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     new [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mactualChannel,[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 actualDescription,[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 [0m[1;35mgetCharset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Charset[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 closeOnError,[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 ignoreLocalFileHeader[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     but after the SSRF patch, the core constructors now expect seven arguments [0m[1;39m([0m[39man[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextra `boolean allowRemoteCommentFetch`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and there is no six-argument overload [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtaking `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel, String, Charset, boolean, boolean, boolean[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. This [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmismatch causes the `Charset`-vs-`String` type error.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Fix Steps[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Update Builder#get to pass the new SSRF flag:[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - In `ZipFile.java`, locate the Builder inner class’s `[0m[1;35mget[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method around [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline [0m[1;36m153[0m[39m.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Change the constructor invocation from six arguments to seven, appending [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe `allowRemoteCommentFetch` flag maintained in the Builder.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```diff[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m before[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return new [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mactualChannel, actualDescription,[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                         [0m[1;35mgetCharset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                         useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                         closeOnError,[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                         ignoreLocalFileHeader[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m after[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return new [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mactualChannel, actualDescription,[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                         [0m[1;35mgetCharset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                         useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                         closeOnError,[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                         ignoreLocalFileHeader,[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                         allowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Verify Other Call Sites[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - All deprecated and public constructors forwarding to the core constructors [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwere already updated in the last patch to supply a default `false` for [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`allowRemoteCommentFetch`. No further changes are needed there.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Preserve Default Behavior[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - By passing `allowRemoteCommentFetch` from Builder [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefaulting to `false`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwe maintain the secure default [0m[1;39m([0m[39mno remote fetch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for code paths not explicitly [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mopting in via `[0m[1;35msetAllowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtrue[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This single-line change restores build compatibility by matching the intended [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mseven-argument constructor.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - It preserves the SSRF mitigation logic by using the `allowRemoteCommentFetch` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mflag to guard remote URL fetches.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - It does not touch any fuzzing harness, tests, or external dependencies, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensuring existing test suites and fuzzer entry points remain intact.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Side Effects & Mitigation[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No new side effects; builder paths now correctly wire through the flag.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing callers of `new [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` that do not use the Builder continue to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefault to `allowRemoteCommentFetch = false`.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No functionality is removed—only constructor wiring is corrected.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. No Additional Files Required[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All relevant code lives in [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`src/main/java/org/apache/commons/compress/archivers/zip/ZipFile.java`.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No external libraries or harness code modifications are needed.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn initial security finding was raised by a Jazzer fuzzer detecting a Server Side [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRequest Forgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in `org.apache.commons.compress.archivers.zip.ZipFile`: when[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreading a ZIP entry comment that begins with “[0m[4;94mhttp://[0m[39m” or “[0m[4;94mhttps://[0m[39m”, the code [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munconditionally opens a remote URL stream. A patch was attempted to introduce a new[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`allowRemoteCommentFetch` flag [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefaulting to false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and to propagate it through [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mall constructors, guarding the remote‐fetch logic behind this flag. After applying [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe patch, the build fails with compilation errors indicating numerous calls to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`new [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` no longer match any available constructor signatures.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The Jazzer report shows a `FuzzerSecurityIssueMedium: Server Side Request [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mForgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` triggered by an attempted connection to `jazze.com:[0m[1;36m80[0m[39m`.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The stack trace leads from the sanitizer check in [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mServerSideRequestForgery.checkSsrfSocket[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` through standard [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mSocket.connect[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mHttpURLConnection.openStream[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, ultimately invoked by [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mZipFile.readCentralDirectoryEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` when processing a ZIP archive comment.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The code in question [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m1548[0m[39m in `ZipFile.java`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m inspects the comment[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstring and, if it starts with “http” or “https”, opens a URL stream, allowing an [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattacker to supply a ZIP with a crafted comment to force the library to fetch [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marbitrary URLs.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A private boolean field `allowRemoteCommentFetch` was added to [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ZipFile.Builder` and to the main `ZipFile` class.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A builder method `[0m[1;35msetAllowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` was introduced.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing public and deprecated `ZipFile` constructors were modified to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maccept the new boolean flag [0m[1;39m([0m[39meither explicitly or by passing `false`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The internal constructor signatures were extended to include the new flag, and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe remote‐fetch conditional was changed to check `allowRemoteCommentFetch` before [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mopening the URL stream.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Two new private helper constructors were added to bridge calls that supply a [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`String`‐based encoding and propagate the flag.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch result and compilation log  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The Maven build fails with two groups of errors at `ZipFile.java:[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m802[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m9[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ZipFile.java:[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m947[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m9[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Each error reports “no suitable constructor found for [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel, String, String, boolean, boolean, boolean[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m”.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The error lists all existing constructors [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthose taking `File`, `Path`, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvarious combinations of charset, booleans, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and none match the new [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msix‐argument signature used at those call sites.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This indicates that some call sites that previously invoked a five‐ or [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mseven‐argument constructor were not updated to the new parameter ordering or count,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand corresponding constructors were not provided to match those exact argument [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlists.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Areas for further investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo resolve the SSRF finding without breaking existing APIs or tests—and to [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meliminate the compilation errors introduced by the last patch—we must [0m[1;39m([0m[39ma[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m wire the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnew allowRemoteCommentFetch flag through every ZipFile constructor and factory [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpath, [0m[1;39m([0m[39mb[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m add the missing constructor overloads so that every `[0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` or `new [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` call resolves, and [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m guard the remote‐fetch logic behind the flag. [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBelow are the step‐by‐step actions.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Core flag field and canonical constructor  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m1.1[0m[39m. In the `ZipFile` class, declare:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        private final boolean allowRemoteCommentFetch;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m1.2[0m[39m. Retain a single “core” private constructor that takes all [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparameters—including the flag—and performs the ZIP population:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        private [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel channel,[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                        String description,[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                        Charset encoding,[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                        boolean useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                        boolean closeOnError,[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                        boolean ignoreLocalFileHeader,[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                        boolean allowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m)[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            this.allowRemoteCommentFetch = allowRemoteCommentFetch;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            … [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m existing init/populateFromCentralDirectory[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. String‐based helper constructor  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Add a private overload to bridge String encodings into the charset‐based core:[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     private [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel channel,[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                     String description,[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                     String encoding,[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                     boolean useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                     boolean closeOnError,[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                     boolean ignoreLocalFileHeader,[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                     boolean allowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m)[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[39mchannel,[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              description,[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[1;35mCharsets.toCharset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mencoding, Builder.DEFAULT_CHARSET[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              closeOnError,[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              ignoreLocalFileHeader,[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              allowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Public/deprecated constructors  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Every public or deprecated constructor must delegate to one of the above two [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverloads, supplying a default `false` for the new flag. For example:[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – File-based constructor:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     @Deprecated[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mFile file, String encoding, boolean useUnicodeExtraFields, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboolean ignoreLocalFileHeader[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mnewReadByteChannel[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mfile.toPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[1;35mfile.getAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              encoding,[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[35m/[0m[39m*closeOnError*[0m[35m/[0m[39m true,[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              ignoreLocalFileHeader,[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[35m/[0m[39m*allowRemoteCommentFetch*[0m[35m/[0m[39m false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Path-based constructor with [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m args:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     @Deprecated[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath path, String encoding, boolean useUnicodeExtraFields, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboolean ignoreLocalFileHeader[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mnewReadByteChannel[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[1;35mpath.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              encoding,[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              true,[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              ignoreLocalFileHeader,[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – SeekableByteChannel overloads [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m boolean flags[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * `public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel channel[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` → delegate `[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…., [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEFAULT_CHARSET_NAME, true, false, false, false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * `public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel channel, String encoding[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` → `[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mencoding, true, false, false, false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * `public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel channel, String desc, String encoding, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboolean useUnicodeExtraFields[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` → `[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…, desc, encoding, useUnicodeExtraFields, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfalse, false, false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * `public [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel channel, String desc, String encoding, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboolean useUnicodeExtraFields, boolean ignoreLocalFileHeader[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` → `[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…, desc, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mencoding, useUnicodeExtraFields, false, ignoreLocalFileHeader, false[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   This ensures that any call to `[0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` or `new [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` matches an existing [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstructor.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Builder support  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m4.1[0m[39m. In `ZipFile.Builder`, add:[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       private boolean allowRemoteCommentFetch = false;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       public Builder [0m[1;35msetAllowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean allow[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           this.allowRemoteCommentFetch = allow;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           return this;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m4.2[0m[39m. In the `[0m[1;35mget[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method, change:[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return new [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mactualChannel,[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                          actualDescription,[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                          [0m[1;35mgetCharset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                          useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                          closeOnError,[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                          ignoreLocalFileHeader[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       to:[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return new [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mactualChannel,[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                          actualDescription,[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                          [0m[1;35mgetCharset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                          useUnicodeExtraFields,[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                          closeOnError,[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                          ignoreLocalFileHeader,[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                          allowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. SSRF guard  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   In `[0m[1;35mreadCentralDirectoryEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, change the unguarded comment fetch:[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"http"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"https"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         … remote fetch …[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   to:[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mallowRemoteCommentFetch[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             && [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"http://"[0m[1;39m)[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 || [0m[1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"https://"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         … remote fetch …[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Verification and side‐effects  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – All existing public and deprecated APIs still exist and default to [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`allowRemoteCommentFetch = false`.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – No tests or harness code changes are required; the API surface and constructor[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverloads are preserved.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – The new flag is off by default, so no behavior changes unless users explicitly[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mopt in.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – The SSRF path is now fully blocked unless [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Builder#[0m[1;35msetAllowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtrue[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is used.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Compilation errors are resolved by providing exact overloads for every [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` invocation.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWith these additions and updates, the build will succeed, all constructor chains [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresolve, and the SSRF vulnerability is mitigated by default.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39morg.apache.commons.compress.archivers.zip.ZipFile.<init>[0m[1;39m([0m[39mZipFile.jav[0m[1;92ma:938[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39morg.apache.commons.compress.archivers.zip.ZipFile.<init>[0m[1;39m([0m[39mZipFile.jav[0m[1;92ma:876[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m[1;35mCompressZipFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCompressZipFuzzer.jav[0m[1;92ma:30[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEDUP_TOKEN: b38823cc610751ee[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn SSRF [0m[1;39m([0m[39mServer Side Request Forgery[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m issue was detected in Apache Commons [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCompress’s `ZipFile` class: when a ZIP entry comment begins with “[0m[4;94mhttp://[0m[39m” or [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“[0m[4;94mhttps://[0m[39m”, the code unconditionally fetched the remote resource. A patch attempt [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madded a new boolean flag [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`allowRemoteCommentFetch`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, defaulting to `false`, to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mgate remote comment fetching via the builder and all `ZipFile` constructors. After [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapplying the patch, the build failed with multiple compilation errors: duplicate [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstructor definitions and mismatched constructor calls with incorrect parameter [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlists.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Jazzer reported `FuzzerSecurityIssueMedium: Server Side Request Forgery [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSSRF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min `ZipFile`.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The vulnerability point was in `[0m[1;35mZipFile.readCentralDirectoryEntry[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1548[0m[39m in the patched file[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m where it checks if the ZIP entry comment starts with [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“http” or “https” and then unconditionally opens an `InputStream` from that URL.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This could allow an attacker to craft a ZIP file whose comment triggers requests [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto internal or sensitive services.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Introduced a private field `allowRemoteCommentFetch` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault `false`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ZipFile`.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Extended the builder [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`ZipFile.Builder`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35msetAllowRemoteCommentFetch[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Modified the main constructor [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand all deprecated overloads[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to accept the new [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mflag, propagating it to the core constructor.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Wrapped the URL fetch logic behind a check `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mallowRemoteCommentFetch && [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcommentString.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"http://"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Updated every overloaded constructor to pass `false` for the new flag.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCompilation Result  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The patch produced multiple `COMPILATION ERROR` messages:  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. **Duplicate constructor definitions** for signatures `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mFile, String, boolean[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mFile, String, boolean, boolean[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, and similarly for `Path` overloads, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating the new constructors clash with existing ones in the class.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. **No suitable constructor found** errors where calls to `[0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` with seven[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor six parameters do not match any constructor signature. This shows the patch [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madded calls expecting new overloads that were never or improperly declared.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKey Log Excerpts  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `constructor [0m[1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mjava.io.File,java.lang.String,boolean[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is already defined in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclass org.apache.commons.compress.archivers.zip.ZipFile`  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `no suitable constructor found for [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mZipFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSeekableByteChannel,String,String,boolean,boolean,boolean[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Constructor Definitions**  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Review all existing `ZipFile` constructors and their signatures. Ensure no [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mduplicate signatures and that each overloaded constructor delegates correctly to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe core implementation.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Check that any new constructor overloads are unique and declared before being [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreferenced.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Chaining and Delegation**  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Verify that each call to `[0m[1;35mthis[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` matches an actual constructor signature, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincluding parameter order and types [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`File`, `Path`, `SeekableByteChannel`, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`String`, `Charset`, booleans[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Consolidate constructor logic where possible to reduce duplication and risk of[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmismatched delegates.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Builder Integration**  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Validate that the builder’s `[0m[1;35mget[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method invokes the correct `ZipFile` [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstructor, matching its new parameter list.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Remote Comment Fetch Logic**  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Audit placement of the `allowRemoteCommentFetch` flag: confirm that the gated [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mURL fetch resides only in the central directory parsing, and no other code paths [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mperform unguarded network access.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBy examining the constructor signatures and their call sites together with the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuilder, the compilation issues can be understood in context and resolved.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
